{"parse":{"title":"Chronicle of the 24 Generals","pageid":29856040,"revid":785072949,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Chronicle of the 24 Generals of the Order of the Friars Minor</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Latin_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Latin language\">Latin</a>: <i><span lang=\"la\">Chronica XXIV Generalium Ordinis Fratrum Minorum</span></i>) is a medieval chronicle written in <a href=\"/wiki/Latin\" title=\"Latin\">Latin</a> around 1370, possibly by the <a href=\"/wiki/Franciscan_monk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Franciscan monk\">Franciscan monk</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Arnaud_de_Sarrant\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arnaud de Sarrant\">Arnaud de Sarrant</a>, though <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ralf_L%C3%BCtzelschwab&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ralf L\u00fctzelschwab (page does not exist)\">Ralf L\u00fctzelschwab</a> doubts this attribution. The work deals with the history of Franciscan Order from its foundation by Saint <a href=\"/wiki/Francis_of_Assisi\" title=\"Francis of Assisi\">Francis of Assisi</a> to <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leonardo_Rossi&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Leonardo Rossi (page does not exist)\">Leonardo Rossi</a> (1373\u20131378), the 24th <a href=\"/wiki/List_of_Ministers_General_of_the_Order_of_Friars_Minor\" title=\"List of Ministers General of the Order of Friars Minor\">Minister General</a> if counting Francis as the first. The chronicle contains detailed accounts of various miracles and martyrs. For example, the Chronicle describes the deaths of <a href=\"/wiki/Berard_of_Carbio\" title=\"Berard of Carbio\">Berard</a> and his companions, the first Franciscan martyrs, killed in Morocco in 1221. Overall, the Chronicle was heavily used by later Franciscan historians.\n</p><p>It is the earliest extant source for the incarceration of <a href=\"/wiki/Roger_Bacon\" title=\"Roger Bacon\">Roger Bacon</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chronicle_of_the_24_Generals&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation encyclopaedia\">Ralf L\u00fctzelschwab (2010). \"Chronica XXIV generalium Ordinis Fratrum Minorum\".  In Graeme Dunphy. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Medieval_Chronicle_Society\" title=\"Medieval Chronicle Society\">Encyclopedia of the Medieval Chronicle</a></i>. Leiden: Brill. p.&#160;451. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/90_04_18464_3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/90 04 18464 3\">90 04 18464 3</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Chronica+XXIV+generalium+Ordinis+Fratrum+Minorum&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+the+Medieval+Chronicle&amp;rft.place=Leiden&amp;rft.pages=451&amp;rft.pub=Brill&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=9004184643&amp;rft.au=Ralf+L%C3%BCtzelschwab&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChronicle+of+the+24+Generals\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chronicle_of_the_24_Generals&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://i-tau.com/wp/?p=382\">Full-text English publication of the chronicle</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2222\nCached time: 20180922102020\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.172 second